This software was originally developed as part of the CLPIC project
(Common Lisp P2P Intellectual Property Chain) and has been extracted
as a standalone library for general use.

The contract DSL provides design-by-contract programming capabilities
for Common Lisp, with support for preconditions, postconditions, type
specifications, and formal verification through proof obligations.

This is a pure Common Lisp implementation with no external dependencies.
